# AI Ascent Hackathon вҖ” Detailed Design Document v1.0

## 1. Overview

### 1.1 Problem Statement
Teams across the organization are independently exploring AI automation opportunities, but there is no centralized system to capture, share, rank, and learn from these initiatives. Knowledge stays siloed, effort gets duplicated, and leadership lacks visibility into the AI adoption landscape.

### 1.2 Solution Summary
Build an end-to-end AI Initiative Management Platform with six integrated components:
1. AI Case Library (structured knowledge base)
2. Learner Input Portal (submission interface)
3. Filterable Browse UI (discovery and search)
4. Analytics Dashboard (insights and trends)
5. Ranking Engine (scoring and leaderboard)
6. AI Solution Design Agent (intelligent recommendation)

### 1.3 Target Users
- Individual contributors submitting AI initiatives
- Program managers tracking team-level AI adoption
- Leadership reviewing aggregate metrics and top initiatives
- New learners seeking inspiration and guidance for AI projects

---

