### 2.2 Technology Choices
| Component | Technology | Rationale |
|-----------|-----------|-----------|
| Frontend | React + Next.js | Fast iteration, SSR for dashboards |
| API | API Gateway + Lambda (or Express) | Serverless, scales to zero |
| Primary DB | DynamoDB | Flexible schema, low-latency reads |
| Vector Store | OpenSearch / Bedrock Knowledge Base | Semantic search for AI Agent |
| AI/ML | Amazon Bedrock (Claude) | Managed LLM, RAG support |
| Analytics | QuickSight or embedded charts (Recharts) | Interactive visualizations |
| Auth | Cognito / Midway | SSO integration |
| Storage | S3 | CSV exports, file attachments |

---

## 3. Component Designs

### 3.1 AI Case Library (Data Model)

#### Schema


| Field | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|-------|------|-------------|-------|
| case_id | String (UUID) | PK, auto-generated | Format: `AI-YYYYMMDD-XXXX` |
| owner_login | String | Required | Submitter's login ID |
| job_level | Enum | Required | L4вҖ“L10 dropdown |
| program_team | String | Required | Free text with autocomplete from existing values |
| use_case_title | String | Required, max 200 chars | Short descriptive title |
| problem_statement | Text | Required, max 2000 chars | What problem does this solve? |
| ai_technique | Enum[] | Required, multi-select | Values: GenAI, ML Classification, NLP, Computer Vision, RAG, Agentic AI, RPA, Other |
| tools_services | String[] | Optional, multi-select | e.g. Bedrock, SageMaker, Q Developer, PartyRock, Lambda, etc. |
| key_prompts | Text | Optional, max 5000 chars | Actual prompts or prompt templates used |
| input_data | Text | Optional, max 2000 chars | Description of input data sources |
| output_outcome | Text | Required, max 2000 chars | What the solution produces |
| time_saved_hours | Number | Optional | Estimated hours saved per week/month |
| accuracy_pct | Number | Optional | Accuracy improvement percentage |
| cost_reduction_pct | Number | Optional | Cost reduction percentage |
| status | Enum | Required | Values: Ideation, POC, Pilot, Production, Deprecated |
| created_date | DateTime | Auto-generated | ISO 8601 |
| updated_date | DateTime | Auto-generated | ISO 8601 |
| rank_score | Number | Auto-calculated | Composite score from ranking engine |
| tags | String[] | Optional | Free-form tags for discoverability |
| attachments | String[] | Optional | S3 keys for uploaded files |

#### Data Seeding
- Import existing AI initiatives from spreadsheets, wikis, and team retrospectives
- Normalize field values (e.g., standardize team names, technique labels)
- Generate embeddings for `problem_statement` + `use_case_title` + `output_outcome` for semantic search

---

### 3.2 Learner Input Portal

#### User Flow
```
[Landing Page] вҶ’ [New Initiative Form] вҶ’ [Draft/Save] вҶ’ [Preview] вҶ’ [Submit]
                                              вҶ“
                                        [My Submissions] вҶ’ [Edit] / [Delete]
```

#### Form Design
- Progressive disclosure: show required fields first, optional fields in expandable sections
- Field-level validation with inline error messages
- Auto-save drafts every 30 seconds
- Rich text editor for `problem_statement`, `output_outcome`, `key_prompts`
- File upload for attachments (max 10MB per file, 5 files per submission)

#### Validation Rules
| Field | Rule |
|-------|------|
| owner_login | Auto-populated from auth session, read-only |
| use_case_title | Required, 10вҖ“200 characters |
| problem_statement | Required, 50вҖ“2000 characters |
| ai_technique | At least one selection required |
| status | Required, default "Ideation" |
| time_saved_hours | If provided, must be > 0 |
| accuracy_pct | If provided, must be 0вҖ“100 |
| cost_reduction_pct | If provided, must be 0вҖ“100 |

#### API Endpoints
| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/initiatives` | Create new initiative (draft or submitted) |
| PUT | `/api/initiatives/{id}` | Update existing initiative |
| DELETE | `/api/initiatives/{id}` | Soft-delete initiative |
| GET | `/api/initiatives/{id}` | Get single initiative |
| GET | `/api/initiatives/mine` | List current user's initiatives |

---

### 3.3 Filterable Browse UI

#### Features
- Server-side paginated table (default 25 rows per page)
- Column sorting (click header to toggle asc/desc)
- Multi-field filter panel (sidebar or top bar):
  - Text search across title + problem statement (full-text)
  - Dropdown filters: program_team, ai_technique, status, job_level
  - Range filters: time_saved_hours, accuracy_pct, cost_reduction_pct
  - Date range filter: created_date
- Saved filter presets (per user)
- Export current filtered view to CSV
- Click-through to initiative detail page

#### API Endpoints
| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/initiatives` | List with query params for filtering, sorting, pagination |
| GET | `/api/initiatives/export` | Export filtered results as CSV (streamed from S3) |

#### Query Parameters
```
?search=text&program=X&technique=GenAI&status=POC
&sort=rank_score&order=desc&page=1&limit=25
```

---

### 3.4 Analytics Dashboard

#### Dashboard Panels

1. Overview Cards (top row)
   - Total initiatives count
   - Initiatives by status (pie/donut chart)
   - Average time saved across all initiatives
   - Top AI technique (most used)

2. By Program/Team (bar chart)
   - X-axis: program/team names
   - Y-axis: count of initiatives
   - Color-coded by status
   - Click to drill down into team's initiatives

3. AI Technique Distribution (horizontal bar or treemap)
   - Count per technique
   - Filterable by status

4. Performance Metrics (scatter plot)
   - X-axis: time_saved_hours
   - Y-axis: accuracy_pct
   - Bubble size: cost_reduction_pct
   - Hover for initiative details

5. Pipeline Funnel (funnel chart)
   - Ideation вҶ’ POC вҶ’ Pilot вҶ’ Production
   - Show conversion rates between stages

6. Trend Over Time (line chart)
   - Monthly submission count
   - Stacked by status or technique

#### Data Refresh
- Real-time for card counts (query on load)
- Dashboard data cached for 5 minutes for chart aggregations
- Manual refresh button available

---

### 3.5 Ranking Engine

#### Scoring Formula
```
rank_score = (w1 Г— impact_score) + (w2 Г— scalability_score) + 
             (w3 Г— efficiency_score) + (w4 Г— innovation_score)
```

#### Score Components

| Component | Calculation | Default Weight |
|-----------|------------|----------------|
| Impact Score (0вҖ“100) | Normalized composite of: time_saved_hours (40%), accuracy_pct (30%), cost_reduction_pct (30%) | w1 = 0.35 |
| Scalability Score (0вҖ“100) | Based on: number of teams that could reuse (manual tag or AI-inferred), breadth of ai_technique applicability | w2 = 0.25 |
| Efficiency Score (0вҖ“100) | Inverse of estimated implementation effort vs. measured impact. Higher score = more bang for buck | w3 = 0.20 |
| Innovation Score (0вҖ“100) | Novelty factor: uniqueness of technique+problem combination relative to existing library entries (cosine distance from nearest neighbor in vector space) | w4 = 0.20 |

#### Leaderboard Features
- Default view: top 20 initiatives by rank_score
- Configurable weights via slider UI (recalculates in real-time)
- Side-by-side comparison: select 2вҖ“3 initiatives to compare across all fields
- Filter leaderboard by program, technique, status
- Badge system: "Top 10", "Most Innovative", "Highest Impact"

#### Recalculation
- Rank scores recalculated nightly via scheduled job
- On-demand recalculation when weights are adjusted in UI (client-side only, not persisted unless admin saves)

---

