        в–ј
в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ  Prompt Construction в”Ӯ вҶҗ System prompt + user query
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
         в”Ӯ
         в–ј
в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ  RAG: Retrieve top-K в”Ӯ вҶҗ Vector search against Case Library embeddings
в”Ӯ  similar cases       в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
         в”Ӯ
         в–ј
в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ  LLM Generation      в”Ӯ вҶҗ Bedrock Claude with retrieved context
в”Ӯ  (Solution Design)   в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
         в”Ӯ
         в–ј
в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ  Structured Output   в”Ӯ вҶ’ Technique, tools, reference cases,
в”Ӯ                      в”Ӯ   effort estimate, implementation steps
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
```

#### System Prompt (Core)
```
You are an AI Solution Design Agent for the AI Ascent program. 
Given a user's problem description, you:
1. Analyze the problem domain and identify the core automation opportunity
2. Search the AI Case Library for similar solved problems
3. Recommend an AI solution design including:
   - Suggested AI technique(s) from: [GenAI, ML Classification, NLP, 
     Computer Vision, RAG, Agentic AI, RPA]
   - Recommended tools/services
   - Reference cases from the library (cite case_id and title)
   - Estimated effort (T-shirt size: S/M/L/XL)
   - Expected outcomes (time saved, accuracy, cost impact)
   - Step-by-step implementation plan
4. Ask clarifying questions if the problem is ambiguous
Always ground recommendations in existing case library data when possible.
Format output in structured markdown.
```

#### RAG Configuration
- Embedding model: Amazon Titan Embeddings v2
- Vector store: OpenSearch Serverless (or Bedrock Knowledge Base)
- Retrieval: top-5 similar cases by cosine similarity
- Minimum similarity threshold: 0.65 (below this, note "no close matches found")
- Context window: include case title, problem statement, technique, tools, outcome for each retrieved case

#### Conversation Flow
1. User describes their problem/scenario
2. Agent retrieves similar cases and generates solution design
3. User can ask follow-up questions to refine:
   - "What if we need this to work in real-time?"
   - "Can you suggest a lower-effort alternative?"
   - "Show me more details on reference case AI-20240315-0042"
4. Agent maintains conversation context for iterative refinement
5. User can save the generated design as a new initiative draft

#### API Endpoints
| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/agent/chat` | Send message, receive agent response |
| GET | `/api/agent/sessions/{id}` | Retrieve conversation history |
| POST | `/api/agent/sessions/{id}/save` | Save design as initiative draft |

---

## 4. Security & Access Control

| Role | Permissions |
|------|------------|
| Viewer | Browse initiatives, view dashboard, use AI Agent |
| Contributor | All Viewer + submit/edit/delete own initiatives |
| Program Admin | All Contributor + edit any initiative in their program, manage program tags |
| Platform Admin | Full access, manage weights, manage users, export all data |

- Authentication via Cognito/Midway SSO
- All API endpoints require valid auth token
- Row-level security: users can only edit/delete their own submissions (unless admin)

---

## 5. Implementation Phases

### Phase 1 вҖ” MVP (Hackathon Scope, 2 days)
- Data model + DynamoDB table
- Input portal (create/edit form)
- Browse UI with basic filtering
- CSV export
- Static ranking (manual score input)

### Phase 2 вҖ” Enhanced (Post-Hackathon, 2 weeks)
- Analytics dashboard with charts
- Automated ranking engine with configurable weights
- Vector embeddings for case library
- AI Agent v1 (single-turn recommendations)

### Phase 3 вҖ” Production (4вҖ“6 weeks)
- Multi-turn AI Agent with conversation memory
- SSO integration
- Role-based access control
- Saved filters and user preferences
- Notification system (new initiatives in your program, rank changes)
- API rate limiting and monitoring

---

## 6. Success Metrics

| Metric | Target |
|--------|--------|
| Initiatives submitted in first month | 50+ |
| Unique users browsing per week | 100+ |
| AI Agent queries per week | 200+ |
| Average time to submit an initiative | < 10 minutes |
| User satisfaction (survey) | > 4.0 / 5.0 |
| Cross-team initiative reuse | 10%+ of initiatives adopted by another team |
